  "type": "mcq",
  "title": "Consumer surplus and Producer surplus",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The market for tomatoes is in equilibrium at the price of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$10\"><math alttext=\"$10\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>10</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and quantity of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50\"><math alttext=\"50\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>50</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> tomatoes. If consumer surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$400\"><math alttext=\"$400\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>400</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and total economic surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$650\"><math alttext=\"$650\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>650</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, what is the producer surplus in the tomato market and why?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The producer surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$0\"><math alttext=\"$0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because producer surplus is offset by the costs of producing tomatoes.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The producer surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$250\"><math alttext=\"$250\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>250</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the total surplus less what consumers receive must go to producers.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The producer surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Negative $400\"><math alttext=\"Negative $400\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mo>−</mo><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>400</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because consumer and producer surplus must offset one another.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The producer surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$500\"><math alttext=\"$500\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>500</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the producer surplus is the equilibrium price times the equilibrium quantity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"equals, $10 times 50, equals $500\"><math alttext=\"equals, $10 times 50, equals $500\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>$</mi><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>$</mi><mn>500</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The producer surplus is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$650\"><math alttext=\"$650\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>$</mi><mn>650</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because producer surplus and total economic surplus are always equal.</p>\n",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
  },
